    <text id="B1230T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Manly authorizes a rent payment for a school building in Staunton.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands,<lb/>Head-Quarters Assistant
                    Commissioner, District of Virginia.
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Brevet Colonel">Bvt. Col.</abbr> Garrick
                            Mallery<lb/><abbr expan="Acting Assistant Adjutant General"
                        >A.A.A.Gen'l</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1869-04-23">April 23, 1869</date>
                        <name type="place">Richmond, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Colonel</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I have the honor to request that rent be paid, at the rate of $17.00 per month
                    from the 1st of April inst. to John Scott of Staunton, Va for the school house
                    used by the American Missionary Association, in that town.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute><abbr expan="Very Respectfully">Very Respy</abbr><lb/>Your <abbr
                            expan="Obedient Servant">Obt Servt</abbr></salute>
                    <signed>R. M. Manly<lb/><abbr expan="Assistant Superintendent">Asst.
                        Supt.</abbr> Schools</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
